!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

horrible /ˈhɒrəbəl, ˈhɒrɪbəl/

1. ADJ If you describe something or someone as horrible , you do not like them at all. 令人讨厌的 [非正式] 

例： Her voice sounds horrible. 她的嗓音难听死了。 

2. horribly ADV 令人讨厌地 [ADV with v] 

例： When trouble comes they behave selfishly and horribly. 困难来临时，他们就表现得很自私，很令人厌恶。 

3. ADJ You can call something horrible when it causes you to feel great shock, fear, and disgust. 令人恐惧的 

例： Still the horrible shrieking came out of his mouth. 吓人的尖叫声还是从他嘴里发出。 

4. horribly ADV 令人恐惧地 [ADV with v] 

例： A two-year-old boy was horribly murdered. 一个两岁的男孩惨遭杀害。 

5. ADJ Horrible is used to emphasize how bad something is. 糟透的 [ADJ n] [强调] 

例： That seems like a horrible mess that will drag on for years. 那看来像是一个将要延续多年的糟糕困境。 

6. horribly ADV 糟透了地 

例： Our plans have gone horribly wrong. 我们的计划已出了大问题。

</div>

